name: Air_B2B_IC_MCCOST
description:
ICA1_AIR: 1 Collect and 1 Prepaid Air HBL traveling on an ICA to its final destination.
  Description: Shipments are based on EUR to US screen flow. At the housebill level: Validate Label Count
  includes Pickup & Delivery costs; edit checks on Rate Class & Custom/Carriage amount.
  HBL1: Currency Code will be Origin's (EUR)
  HBL2: Currency Code will be updated to Destination's (USD)
  For Housebills: The invoice screen will show GL 4002, P/UA, ISS, FSC and 4001. These cover the check for Freight Revenue(4002),
  Pickup & Destination, Billing codes mapped to Freight Rev (ISS, FSC), and GLs NOT matched to Freight Revenue
  At Consol level: ICCOST and HBCOST processing adding airport transfer & destin fees, and additional costs (onforwarding fee & cost, and CFS fee)

name: Air_DC_IC_Gtwy_MCCOST_Correx
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway - QA1/MIL
  Destination - QA1/DEN

  NOTE: 
  While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
  In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa


  Steps:
  Process Air_DC_IC_MCCOST.feature all the way through posting consol settlement at CFIT destination
  Log into CFIT origin and go to Pay from Invoice screen to validate ESJV (NOTE: ES after posting DC)
  Enter DCANUM in invoice_No field and hit SELECT
  Validate all contents are correct
  Select check_no_1 field (i.e CHK/JV# column) and hit F4 (View JV)
  Validate all contents are correct
  Log into EIFA gateway to validate ESJV (NOTE: ES for posting DC Destin Cost at gateway)
  Enter 3 in SELECTION_NO field and hit Enter key
  Enter 1 in SELECTION_NO field and hit Enter key
  Enter DCANUM in JOURNAL field and hit Enter key
  Validate all the contents. Notice there are 2 pages. DISPLAY_REV_06 field says "Journal 1 of 2"
  Hit F2
  Validate all contents
  Log into CFIT gateway - Option 2-->INVOICE ACCOUNTING
  Click to Option 3 -->Pay from Invoice
  Enter ICANUM in invoice_No field and hit F7/SELECT (NOTE: ES for posting IC)
  Validate all contents
  Select check_No1 line and click F4/ViewJV)
  Validate all the contents here

  Data:
  EHA1  prepaid  VRNDEN (Rate in local currency (EUR) and bill in foreign currency (USD))
  EHA2  collect  VRN-DEN (Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD))
  EHA3  prepaid  MILDEN (Rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  DCA  VRN-MIL
  ICA  MIL-DEN

name: AIR_GC_IC_Functional
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway - QA4/YYC
  Destination - QA1/DEN

  NOTE:

   While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charges/rates)
   In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa

  Steps:

  1. Run Air GC-IC_MCCOST automation script all the way through posting consol settlement at the destination
  2. Go to CFIT destination consol settlement screen and validate all fields including reason_Label field. Validate the suffix should be 02
  3. Grab and save master_invoice number for later use
  4. While in CFIT destination -->click Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING
  5. Click on Option 11 AR History by Invoice
  6. Enter master_invoice# from step 3 in invoice_No field
  7. Click F7/SELECT INVOICE
  8. Validate all contents (NOTE: Invoice to service requesting branch)
  9. Grab and save E# from action1 line
  10. Click on action1 line and select F2/REVIEW INVOICE
  11. Validate all the contents
  12. Go to CFIT gateway-->Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING
  13. Click on Option 28 - Review Vendor Invoice
  14. Enter E# from action3 line from step 9 in vendor_Inv_No field and hit F2/FIND
  15. Validate all the contents (NOTE: payable to destination)
  16. Stay in CFIT gateway and go to the main page.
  17. click Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING and Click on Option 11 AR History by Invoice
  18. Enter ICANUM in invoice_No field and hit F7 (SELECT INVOICE) (NOTE: Invoice to origin)
  19. Validate all the contents
  20. Save all the E# (action1, action2 lines) under Event column. They are needed for later useValidate all content
  21. Log into EIFA gateway (QA1/YYZ). In SELECTION_NO, enter 3 and hit Enter key. Again in SELECTION_NO, enter 1 and hit Enter key
  22. In JOURNAL field enter ICANUM and hit Enter key
  23. Validate all fields in this screen including DISPLAY_REV_06 field. Hit Next Page and validate all fields ( NOTE: ES at gateway for IC after posting IC)
  24. Stay in EIFA gateway, Exit one time from the current screen to go back to the MENU_SCREEN #S1060.
  25. In SELECTION_NO, enter 1 and hit Enter key
  26. In JOURNAL field enter DCANUM number and hit Enter key (NOTE: ES at gateway after posting DC destin cost)
  27. Validate all contents
  28. Go to CFIT origin -->Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTING (NOTE: payable to gateway for the invoice sent in steps 16-19)
  29. Click on Option 28 - Review Vendor Invoice
  30. Enter E# from from step 20 in vendor_Inv_No field and hit F2/FIND. Need to do for each E#
  31. Validate all the contents
  32. Click EXIT button and repeat steps 28 and 29. Repeat for the rest of the E# saved from step 20
  33. Validate all the contents
  34. Go to CFIT Origin and click Option 2 - INVOICE ACCOUNTIN
  35. Click on Option 3 -->Pay from Invoice and enter DCANUM in invoice_No field and hit F7/SELECT (NOTE: ES at origin after posting GC)
  36. validate all contents

  Data:
  EHA1  prepaid  VRNDEN (Rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  EHA2  collect  VRN-DEN (Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD))
  EHA3  prepaid  YYCDEN (Rate and bill in local currency (CAD))
  DCA  VRN-YYC
  ICA  YYC-DEN

name: Air_IC_IC_Functional
description:
Create a happy path end-to-end automation script that runs in the given QA Environments without errors.
  Origin - QA3/VRN
  Gateway - QA1/DEN
  Destination - QA4/YYC

  NOTE: 
  While processing shipments, enter amounts into every costs field/s available (charge/rates)
  In case of prepaid, rate and bill can be in different currencies. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill in foreign currency (INV screen)
  In case of collect, rate and bill should be in same currency. Example rate in local currency (AWBHDR screen) and bill should be in local currency as well (INV screen) or vice versa

  Steps:
  1. Process a prepaid house air shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in local currency (EUR)
  2. Process a collect house air shipment from origin to destination. Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD)
  3. Process EHA shipment to INV
  4.Create invoice that has a mix of freight revenue GL's, billing codes mapped to freight revenue and other GL's not mapped to freight revenue
  5. Finish the shipments by printing on AWBPRT
  6.Confirm CFDATA is clear at Origin
  7. Attach the housebills to an IC destined to gateway
  8. Print the MNFST
  9. Post MCTRAN
  Find on IC reference in CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  Receive ShipLog at gateway CFIT and post the consol settlement
  Receive ShipLog at destination CFIT and post the consol settlement
  Find on origin IC reference in gateway DCLOG screen
  Enter receiving information and hit F1/Add Modify
  Find on IC references in gateway CFDATA and make sure it is clear
  Process a collect house air shipment from gateway to final destination. Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD)
  In gateway consol, attach the original HBLs and a new collect house air shipment to an ICA destined to final destination
  Print MNFST
  Process ICCOST, HBCOST and post MCTRAN
  Make sure CFDATA is clear
  Receive ShipLog at CFIT destination and post the consol settlement

  Data:
  EHA1  prepaid  VRNYYC (Rate and bill in local currency (EUR))
  EHA2  collect  VRN-YYC (Rate and bill in foreign currency (USD))
  EHA3  collect  DENYYC (Rate and bill in foreign currency (CAD))
  ICA  VRN-DEN
  ICA  DEN-YYC
